    "body": "@JustinZhengBC The `pd.DataFrame(df)` instead of `pd.SparseDataFrame(df)` is on purpose, as I was testing the sparse support in a *normal* DataFrame. That was not fully clear from the issue.\r\n\r\nNormal DataFrames also support storing sparse columns in it:\r\n\r\n```\r\nIn [14]: type(df2)                                                                                                                                                              \r\nOut[14]: pandas.core.frame.DataFrame\r\n\r\nIn [15]: df2.dtypes                                                                                                                                                             \r\nOut[15]: \r\na    Sparse[int64, 0]\r\nb    Sparse[int64, 0]\r\nc    Sparse[int64, 0]\r\ndtype: object\r\n```"
